<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="608" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11 G93/461.]</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Plaza stated this morning that the mortgages would not be paid
                            unless the railway compromised the revolutionary bills, average last six
                            months last year plus fifty per cent, plus 65,000 sucres damages;
                            questions relating to interest, and approval of bills previously passed
                            by Minister of Interior, to be referred to arbitration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>